      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model inputs documented with sources; uncertain inputs identified and bounds specified; UQ performed via Monte Carlo propagation.",
      "rationale": "Thirteen model inputs catalogued in simulation plan with nominal values and sources. Key uncertain inputs — inlet flow rate (±3%), rotational speed (±1%), blood viscosity (±8%), and hemolysis model exponents α and β — assigned probability distributions from published literature. Monte Carlo UQ (N=2000 samples) propagated through reduced-order surrogate to generate output distributions. The UQ report includes a verbal summary of a screening sensitivity study that ranked viscosity and model exponent β as dominant contributors to NIH variance. Predicted RH remains below 1.0 at the 95th percentile for all five operating points, confirming margin against acceptance criterion."
