    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed their required gradation levels for MRL 2. Six factors appropriately scoped out per MRL 2 assessment matrix. Monte Carlo UQ confirms RH < 1.0 at 95th percentile across all five COU operating points, satisfying the regulatory acceptance criterion. The UQ report references a screening sensitivity study identifying viscosity and hemolysis model exponent β as dominant variance contributors; this information is incorporated into the model inputs factor rationale. The credibility assessment team concludes that the CFD model provides adequate evidence to support the submission claim that the CPB device does not exceed predicate hemolysis performance.",
